FBIS3-48438 "dreas017_c_94009" FBIS-EAS-94-017 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Jan 1994 North Korea ROK Party To Form Human Rights Committee SK2601102494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1003 GMT 26 Jan 94 SK2601102494 Pyongyang KCNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Pyongyang, January 26 (KCNA) -- The opposition Democratic Party of South Korea at a caucus meeting Monday decided to inaugurate a measure committee based on the human rights committee of the party to promote the release of all the prisoners of conscience, a Seoul-based radio reported. The Democratic Party paid high tribute to the reunification will of the late Rev. Mun Ik-hwan and repeatedly urged the authorities to pardon and reinstate him.
